    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="190"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.21/327</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Thomson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Colombian Government and public growing restless and impatient at the delay of
                    the Senate in considering the Colombian treaty. I have received long and
                    forceful note from Minister of Foreign Affairs urging action. Special message
                    from the President at the earliest practical moment will relieve tension.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thomson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
